On 2/19/05 7:54 PM, "Sami Dakhlia" <sdakhlia(-at-)cba.ua.edu> wrote:

> Hi,
> 
> I'm trying to pull the fan from a type 4 fan housing. I removed the 3
> bolts and have tried using a harmonic puller, but the fan will not come
> off. Now, I applied some moderate torque on the puller, not too much
> for fear of breaking something. Before I try harder, can someone tell
> me if I'm missing something?
> 
> TIA,
> 
> Sami

Sami,

Once the 3 screws are removed, the fan is free, it should almost fall off.
There might be some rust and crud holding it on, but a few whacks with a
rubber mallet around the pulley rim should free it up.

